author: Philip Bump
title: How mortality predictions in a leading coronavirus model dropped over time
description: In some states, the actual death toll was a fraction of what the model predicted.
content:
Happily, that estimate was wrong. As of Monday, according to data from Johns Hopkins University, only about 100 Alabamians have died of the disease.
